= Endings =

'''Chrono Trigger''' features multiple endings depending on when and how Lavos is defeated. The game has 13 distinct endings (14 in DS/PC versions), encouraging multiple playthroughs.

__TOC__

== Ending Requirements ==

The ending you receive depends on:
* When you defeat Lavos (point in story)
* Whether Crono is alive
* Which characters are in your party
* Specific story flags

== Main Endings ==

=== Ending 1: Beyond Time ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after reviving Crono at Death Peak

The canonical "best" ending. Shows:
* Crono's mother wakes him up
* Festival day at Leene Square
* Party says goodbye at the fair
* Time Gate opens, party chases Crono's cat
* Crono, Marle, and Lucca fly through time
* Credits show characters in their eras
* Epoch flies toward balloon in moonlight

=== Ending 2: Reunion ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos without reviving Crono (after visiting Death Peak)

* Similar to Beyond Time
* Marle's pendant reacts at the telepod
* Marle searches for Crono through time
* Different credits sequence
* "The search for Crono" theme

=== Ending 3: The Dream Project ===

'''Requirement:''' New Game+, defeat Lavos at beginning via telepod

The developer room ending:
* Access room with sprites of development team
* Talk to "Square Soft" developers
* Hidden messages and jokes
* Credits play differently

== New Game+ Endings ==

=== Ending 4: The Successor of Guardia ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after saving Leene but before trial

* Frog is shown as legendary hero
* Glenn receives recognition
* Marriage-related scenes

=== Ending 5: Good Night ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after trial but before time travel begins

* Nu and Ribbit discuss game
* "Good night" message
* Developer in-joke ending

=== Ending 6: The Legendary Hero ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after arriving in 600 A.D. first time, before Tata events

* Tata is proclaimed hero
* Frog remains in hiding
* Alternate history plays out

=== Ending 7: The Unknown Past ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after meeting Frog but before getting Masamune

* Robo takes over as ruler of future
* Mankind never evolved
* Dark comedy ending

=== Ending 8: People of the Times ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after getting Masamune but before Magus battle

* Crono and Marle see old footage
* Shows prehistoric humans
* Reptites won instead

=== Ending 9: The Oath ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after defeating Magus (first time)

* Frog confronts Magus
* Dramatic battle scene
* Resolution of their conflict

=== Ending 10: Dino Age ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after facing Azala

* Reptites rule Earth
* Human evolution never occurred
* Reptite society flourishes

=== Ending 11: What the Prophet Seeks ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after arriving in Dark Ages

* Magus scenes
* His true motivations revealed
* Schala subplot

=== Ending 12: Memory Lane ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Lavos after Crono dies at Ocean Palace

* Slideshow of adventure
* Memories of Crono
* Bittersweet ending

=== Ending 13: Dream's Epilogue ===

'''Requirement:''' Defeat Dream Devourer (DS/PC only)

* Magus confronts Dream Devourer
* Schala-related content
* Setup for Chrono Cross
* DS/PC exclusive

